column5: 0. Open file in Excel (or whatever can handle Excel-equivalent formulas).
column6: Note: This formula has been verified to work correctly on Google Sheets. One should spot-check it anyway, just to be sure.

column5: 1. If F1 is text (starts with apostrophe), change it to a formula (starts with =). See #N/A.
column6: Note: If more combinations of nwar are found, change the formula range (currently $A$2:$A$7) accordingly.

column5: 2. Copy F1 to cells F9 through F(end); cell references: A1 becomes A9, $A$1 stays $A$1.
column6: Note: If you add entries, make sure that you don't have cafe autocorrecting to café (amenity). In Excel: logo menu, Excel Options, Proofing, AutoCorrect Options, Replace text as you type.

column5: 3. Confirm a few lines of JSON are correct, especially the nwar object types expansions.
column6: Note: Don't forget to remove the comma at the end of the last JSON entry after copy/pasting!

column5: 4. Copy/paste resulting JSON text in cells to your favorite editor. Remove last comma.
